{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-article-template-js","path":"/social-cards-with-gatsby","result":{"data":{"BlogPostByPath":{"html":"<p>As I've been sharing links more often from my website, I noticed that when I would share a link over text or slack that the social card could be improved.</p>\n<h2 id=\"starting-point\" style=\"position:relative;\">Starting point<a href=\"#starting-point\" aria-label=\"starting point permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/0da2ab78260a3b67a00eac92bd707620/c3e7c/starting-point.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 700px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 74.85714285714286%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Starting point for social sharing card\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/0da2ab78260a3b67a00eac92bd707620/d3c05/starting-point.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/0da2ab78260a3b67a00eac92bd707620/8ac2c/starting-point.png 175w,\n/static/0da2ab78260a3b67a00eac92bd707620/8fa76/starting-point.png 350w,\n/static/0da2ab78260a3b67a00eac92bd707620/d3c05/starting-point.png 700w,\n/static/0da2ab78260a3b67a00eac92bd707620/c3e7c/starting-point.png 892w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<br />\n<p>Observations</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The image is the same default site image every time I share an article, even though each article has a custom image</li>\n<li>The titles of the articles don't show - only the site title</li>\n<li>The description displayed is the one for the site, I'd like to have it display a summary of each article instead</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"approach\" style=\"position:relative;\">Approach<a href=\"#approach\" aria-label=\"approach permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<p>I'm going to tackle this piece by piece. First I did some research to understand what is ahead so I can make a plan. Here are the options I found:</p>\n<h3 id=\"option-1-no-custom-photos-but-programmatically-generated-text-to-image\" style=\"position:relative;\">Option 1: No custom photos, but programmatically generated text to image<a href=\"#option-1-no-custom-photos-but-programmatically-generated-text-to-image\" aria-label=\"option 1 no custom photos but programmatically generated text to image permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gatsbyjs.com/plugins/gatsby-remark-social-cards/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">gatsby-remark-social-cards</a></p>\n<p>There's a also good series from Learn with Jason <a href=\"https://www.learnwithjason.dev/blog/design-social-sharing-card/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Part 1</a> and <a href=\"https://www.learnwithjason.dev/blog/auto-generate-social-image/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Part 2</a> and the resulting npm package <a href=\"https://www.npmjs.com/package/@jlengstorf/get-share-image\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">get-share-image</a></p>\n<h3 id=\"option-2-custom-photo-with-custom-overlay-area-with-text\" style=\"position:relative;\">Option 2: Custom photo, with custom overlay area with text<a href=\"#option-2-custom-photo-with-custom-overlay-area-with-text\" aria-label=\"option 2 custom photo with custom overlay area with text permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"%5Bhttps://www.gatsbyjs.com/plugins/gatsby-plugin-social-cards/%5D(https://www.gatsbyjs.com/plugins/gatsby-plugin-social-cards/)\">gatsby-plugin-social-cards</a></p>\n<h3 id=\"option-3-custom-photos-with-no-text-overlay\" style=\"position:relative;\">Option 3: Custom photos with no text overlay<a href=\"#option-3-custom-photos-with-no-text-overlay\" aria-label=\"option 3 custom photos with no text overlay permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://juliangaramendy.dev/blog/custom-open-graph-images-in-gatsby-blog\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Custom image with default fallback</a></p>\n<h2 id=\"selection\" style=\"position:relative;\">Selection<a href=\"#selection\" aria-label=\"selection permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<p>I opted to go with option 3 because it was most important to me to have the unique article image (that I photographed!) display with each link. I didn't want text to overlay the image, but I did want the article title and description to display.</p>\n<h2 id=\"implementation\" style=\"position:relative;\">Implementation<a href=\"#implementation\" aria-label=\"implementation permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<h3 id=\"1-add-a-prop-to-the-layout-component-to-take-in-the-frontmatter-for-the-article-image\" style=\"position:relative;\">1. Add a prop to the layout component to take in the frontmatter for the article image.<a href=\"#1-add-a-prop-to-the-layout-component-to-take-in-the-frontmatter-for-the-article-image\" aria-label=\"1 add a prop to the layout component to take in the frontmatter for the article image permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h3>\n<p>I already had the image in the frontmatter</p>\n<pre><code>featuredImage: \"IMG_1234.jpg\"\n</code></pre>\n<p>I added this to my <code>articleTemplate.js</code> file and pass <code>image</code> as a prop into my layout component.</p>\n<pre><code>//articleTemplate.js\n\nconst { featuredImage } = frontmatter\nconst ogImagePath = featuredImage &#x26;&#x26; featuredImage.childImageSharp.fixed.src\n\n...\n\nreturn (\n  &#x3C;LayoutMain title={`${frontmatter.title} | By Jules Chevalier`} image={ogImagePath}>\n  ...\n  &#x3C;/LayoutMain>\n)\n</code></pre>\n<p>I already was using the site thumbnail as the image for the social card, so I added the new image from props and if that doesn't exist, it will default back to the site image.</p>\n<pre><code>// layout-main.js\n&#x3C;meta\n  property=\"og:image\"\n  content={\n    props.image\n      ? `https://juleschevalier.com${props.image}`\n      : data.site.siteMetadata.thumbnail\n  }\n/>\n\n&#x3C;meta\n  name=\"twitter:image\"\n  content={\n    props.image\n      ? `https://juleschevalier.com${props.image}`\n      : data.site.siteMetadata.thumbnail\n  }\n/>\n</code></pre>\n<p>‚ö†Ô∏è Note the reason for not using just <code>props.image</code> is that is only a partial path from the root url. You need to add your domain name for the image to be reachable.</p>\n<h3 id=\"2-crop-the-article-images-with-different-aspect-ratio\" style=\"position:relative;\">2. Crop the article images with different aspect ratio<a href=\"#2-crop-the-article-images-with-different-aspect-ratio\" aria-label=\"2 crop the article images with different aspect ratio permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h3>\n<p>I realized that the images were not the right size, so they weren't showing up in the validators. According to <a href=\"https://css-tricks.com/essential-meta-tags-social-media/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">CSS Tricks</a></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>[The image] should be at least 600√ó315 pixels, but 1200√ó630 or larger is preferred (up to 5MB). Stay close to a 1.91:1 aspect ratio to avoid cropping.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I was using the same image for the article photo, but that had a different aspect ratio (1.5).</p>\n<p>I was able to add a new query in <code>articleTemplate.js</code> for the social image, cropping to 1200 x 630. I used a fixed query for this. Next, I noticed the crops of the images were not in the center, which I didn't like. Looking into gatsby image query params, I noticed it uses <code>gatsby-plugin-sharp</code> which has <code>cropFocus</code> and <code>fit</code> as options.</p>\n<pre><code>export const pageQuery = graphql`\n  query($path: String!) {\n    BlogPostByPath: markdownRemark(frontmatter: { path: { eq: $path } }) {\n      html\n      frontmatter {\n        date(formatString: \"MMMM Do, YYYY\")\n        path\n        title\n        topic\n        featuredImage {\n          childImageSharp {\n            fluid(maxWidth: 860, quality: 75) {\n              ...GatsbyImageSharpFluid\n            }\n          }\n        }\n      }\n    }\n    SocialImage: markdownRemark(frontmatter: { path: { eq: $path } }) {\n      frontmatter {\n        featuredImage {\n          childImageSharp {\n            fixed(width: 1200, height: 630, cropFocus: CENTER, quality: 50) {\n              ...GatsbyImageSharpFixed\n            }\n          }\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  }\n`\n</code></pre>\n<h3 id=\"3-update-the-card-title-to-the-article-title\" style=\"position:relative;\">3. Update the card title to the article title<a href=\"#3-update-the-card-title-to-the-article-title\" aria-label=\"3 update the card title to the article title permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h3>\n<p>Since the title of the article was already getting passed to the layout component for the page title, I just had to add the option for the social cards</p>\n<pre><code>// layout-main.js\n&#x3C;meta property=\"og:title\" content={props.title || data.site.siteMetadata.title} />\n...\n&#x3C;meta name=\"twitter:title\" content={props.title || data.site.siteMetadata.title} />\n</code></pre>\n<h3 id=\"4-descriptions\" style=\"position:relative;\">4. Descriptions<a href=\"#4-descriptions\" aria-label=\"4 descriptions permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h3>\n<p>Next, I wanted to have a short description or summary of each post that I could use for the cards that display it. Twitter, Facebook and search use this. LinkedIn and iMessage does not.</p>\n<p>I started by adding a new field to frontmatter called <code>summary</code> and added that to each article. It seems for SEO the <a href=\"https://moz.com/learn/seo/meta-description\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">character max is 160</a>.</p>\n<pre><code>// articleTemplate.js\n&#x3C;Layout\n  ...\n  description={frontmatter.summary}\n>\n</code></pre>\n<p>Then I added it to both the open graph and twitter descriptions. It was already an option for the page description, but I am showing that also for consistency sake.</p>\n<pre><code>// layout-main.js\n&#x3C;meta\n  name=\"description\"\n  content={props.description || data.site.siteMetadata.description}\n/>\n\n&#x3C;meta\n  property=\"og:description\"\n  content={props.description || data.site.siteMetadata.description}\n/>\n\n&#x3C;meta\n  name=\"twitter:description\"\n  content={props.description || data.site.siteMetadata.description}\n/>\n</code></pre>\n<h2 id=\"testing\" style=\"position:relative;\">Testing<a href=\"#testing\" aria-label=\"testing permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<p>To test on localhost, I found a lot of mentions to use <code>ngrok</code> which I have found super useful in the past. I couldn't get any of the validators to successfully load the cards though (even though the links were working).</p>\n<p>So of course I pushed to production üôà to test. ¬Ø\\_(„ÉÑ)_/¬Ø</p>\n<h3 id=\"sites-i-used-for-testing\" style=\"position:relative;\">Sites I used for testing:<a href=\"#sites-i-used-for-testing\" aria-label=\"sites i used for testing permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://debug.iframely.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">iframely</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://cards-dev.twitter.com/validator\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">twitter card validator</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://developers.facebook.com/tools/debug/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">facebook sharing debugger</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/post-inspector/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">linkedin post inspector</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>‚ö†Ô∏è you need an account and to be logged in for these to work (except iframely)</p>\n<h2 id=\"adjustments\" style=\"position:relative;\">Adjustments<a href=\"#adjustments\" aria-label=\"adjustments permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<p>I realized that I had been missing a few open graph tags when testing on facebook and linkedin. I added <code>og:type</code> for <code>article</code> and updated the <code>og:url</code> to link to the specific article and not the homepage.</p>\n<p>This is an excellent reference for the html <a href=\"https://htmlhead.dev\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">head tag</a></p>\n<p>I had trouble with LinkedIn showing the updates, apparently they cache previews for 7 days.</p>\n<h2 id=\"result\" style=\"position:relative;\">Result<a href=\"#result\" aria-label=\"result permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/66dc70d46b2947df63734802095a3016/4ae3e/result.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 700px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 75.99999999999999%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Result of completed feature\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/66dc70d46b2947df63734802095a3016/d3c05/result.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/66dc70d46b2947df63734802095a3016/8ac2c/result.png 175w,\n/static/66dc70d46b2947df63734802095a3016/8fa76/result.png 350w,\n/static/66dc70d46b2947df63734802095a3016/d3c05/result.png 700w,\n/static/66dc70d46b2947df63734802095a3016/4ae3e/result.png 890w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>Now each time I share an article, the image is what a reader will see when they click the link. Additionally the card has a correct title and description, so they have a sense of what the link will show them.</p>","frontmatter":{"date":"March 31st, 2021","path":"/social-cards-with-gatsby","title":"Custom Social Sharing Cards With Gatsby","summary":"How to set up large custom previews when you share your links on social platforms.","topic":"Technology","featuredImageAlt":"A unique rock with naturally occurring line markings that is sitting surrounded by sand.","featuredImage":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1.5034965034965035,"src":"/static/183ceebe1b0767dd32cb8c72c23f793b/52efb/IMG_0815.jpg","srcSet":"/static/183ceebe1b0767dd32cb8c72c23f793b/f5236/IMG_0815.jpg 215w,\n/static/183ceebe1b0767dd32cb8c72c23f793b/9865e/IMG_0815.jpg 430w,\n/static/183ceebe1b0767dd32cb8c72c23f793b/52efb/IMG_0815.jpg 860w,\n/static/183ceebe1b0767dd32cb8c72c23f793b/c26c2/IMG_0815.jpg 1200w","sizes":"(max-width: 860px) 100vw, 860px"}}}}},"SocialImage":{"frontmatter":{"featuredImage":{"childImageSharp":{"fixed":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","width":1200,"height":630,"src":"/static/183ceebe1b0767dd32cb8c72c23f793b/0eab3/IMG_0815.jpg","srcSet":"/static/183ceebe1b0767dd32cb8c72c23f793b/0eab3/IMG_0815.jpg 1x"}}}}}},"pageContext":{}}}